result.execSummary:
The defendant Alicia L Larson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Restitution is to be paid within the first six (6) months of probation. Defendant to file state and federal taxes on or before April 1st of each year and surrender any refunds for restitution and provide a copy of filings to P&P.

The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.

Defendant to provide any disability records to P&P in regards to employment.

Defendant may not consume/possess any alcohol.

Defendant may not enter any bar/taverns.

Defendant may not have any contact with victim (L.G.) or her family or any property owned or occupied by them.

Defendant must take all medications as prescribed and in the manner in which they are prescribed by her treating physician.

Defendant is to undergo anger management assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

Defendant Alicia L Larson in court with attorney Steven G. Richards.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 11:22 AM. Richards has revocation paperwork, states one concern in regards to the narrative but otherwise no inaccuracies or errors. State sees no inaccuracies or errors. State wants to look into the credit due to the recent revocation in Vilas County (96 days). Richards agrees that the defendant received the 96 days in the Vilas County case. Discussion on credit/dual credit - Richardson can review the credit issue. State makes final argument prior to its recommendation - recommends 8 months in jail on both counts (#1 and #3 - concurrent to each other. Richard makes final argument prior to recommendation. Larson makes statement. Court sentences the defendant to the following: counts #1 and #3 - 5 months in FC jail - concurrent to each other - huber and good time allowed - eligible for community service under 973.03(3) - report today - credit for 2 days on each count and Richards can review it if he feels more is due, turn any unpaid fines into civil judgment, right to appeal, adjourned.
Sentencing hearing on revocation on September 14, 2017 at 11:00 am.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Alicia L Larson in court with attorney Chad Lynch.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 11:23 AM. State - resolved. Lynch agrees and provides court with plea questionnaire  - State - defendant to plead G/NC to count #1 as alleged and #3 as alleged, DRI #2 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 18 months on each count - concurrent to each other, #1 - pay restitution of $622.38 to victim plus $62.23 in VW surcharge for a total restitution of $684.61 - to be paid within first 6 months of probation - file state and federal income taxes, court costs only on each count, have complied with victim notification requirements and victim is in courtroom, AODA and follow thru, anger management and follow thru, absolute sobreity, no possession of alcohol and no entry into any bars, taverns or class B establishments, maintain/obtain full time employment/school, 80 hours of community service, take all meds as prescribed, no contact with victim (L.G. or Lot 18 on Cobb Blvd, Crandon, WI). Lynch and Larson agree. Larson pleads NC to counts #1 and #3 as alleged. Court dismisses and reads in count #2. Court has plea questionnare, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her constitutional rights by entering her plea, right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Lynch makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Larson makes statement, remorseful. Victim makes statement. Court sentences the defendant to the following: counts #1 and #3 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 18 months on each count - concurrent to each other, with conditions of: costs on each count - paid thru probation, #1 - restitution of $684.61 (including victim/witness surcharge) - finds that the defendant has the ability to pay the restitution and it is to be paid within the first 6 months of probation and defendant to file state and federal taxes on or before April 1st of each year and surrender any returns for restitution and provide a copy of filings to P&P, AODA and follow thru, anger management and follow thru, maintain/obtain full time employment/school - to provide any disability records to P&P in regards to employment, 80 hours of community service - to be completed within the first 6 months of probation, no possession or consumption of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, no contact with victim (L.G.) or her family or any property owned or occupied by them, take all medications as precribed and in the manner in which they are prescribed by her treating physician, 90 days in FC jail - stayed - if restitution if not paid within 6 months - must serve 90 days in jail - huber allowed, submit DNA sample, right to appeal, adjourned.
